---
/** Side-by-side comparison matching guide table content. */
---

<figure class="content-figure data-figure">
  <div class="fig-inner" role="img" aria-label="Comparison of certificate of deposit versus high-yield savings account">
    <p class="fig-title">CD vs high-yield savings</p>
    <div class="cols">
      <div class="card-col cd">
        <div class="head">
          <span class="badge lock">Locked term</span>
          <h3>Certificate of deposit</h3>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Rate</strong> Often fixed for the full term</li>
          <li><strong>Access</strong> Limited until maturity; early exit usually costs a penalty</li>
          <li><strong>Best for</strong> Money you won’t need until a known date</li>
          <li><strong>Predictability</strong> High if held to maturity</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card-col hy">
        <div class="head">
          <span class="badge flex">Flexible</span>
          <h3>High-yield savings</h3>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Rate</strong> Variable — bank can change APY</li>
          <li><strong>Access</strong> Easy transfers and withdrawals (product rules apply)</li>
          <li><strong>Best for</strong> Emergency fund & near-term goals</li>
          <li><strong>Predictability</strong> Lower — rates move with the market</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="tradeoff">
      Core tradeoff: <strong>rate certainty vs liquidity</strong>. Use the CD calculator for locked-term growth; keep
      emergency cash liquid.
    </p>
  </div>
  <figcaption>
    General product-structure summary for education. Not a recommendation. Confirm terms and insurance with your
    institution (FDIC or NCUA as applicable).
  </figcaption>
</figure>

<style>
  .fig-inner {
    padding: 20px;
  }
  .fig-title {
    margin: 0 0 14px;
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-graphite);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }
  .cols {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 12px;
  }
  .card-col {
    border: 1px solid var(--color-pale-slate);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 14px;
    background: #fff;
  }
  .card-col.cd {
    border-color: #c9daf8;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #f0f5fe 0%, #fff 50%);
  }
  .card-col.hy {
    border-color: #c6ebd5;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #f3fcf6 0%, #fff 50%);
  }
  .head h3 {
    margin: 8px 0 12px;
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }
  .badge {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 3px 8px;
    border-radius: 9999px;
  }
  .badge.lock {
    background: #e8f0fe;
    color: var(--color-midnight-iris);
  }
  .badge.flex {
    background: #e6f8ee;
    color: #1a7a45;
  }
  .card-col ul {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .card-col li {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--color-iron);
    line-height: 1.45;
    margin: 0 0 10px;
    padding-bottom: 10px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-pale-slate);
  }
  .card-col li:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
    padding-bottom: 0;
    border-bottom: none;
  }
  .card-col li strong {
    display: block;
    font-size: 11px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: var(--color-graphite);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 2px;
  }
  .tradeoff {
    margin: 14px 0 0;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--color-iron);
    line-height: 1.5;
    padding: 12px;
    background: #fafcfe;
    border-radius: 6px;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-pale-slate);
  }
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .cols {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
